HEADWORD: Discure
<hw>Dis*cure"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Discover</er>.]</ety> <def>To discover; to reveal; to
discoure.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will, if please you it <qex>discure</qex>, assay⟦br⟧
To ease you of that ill, so wisely as I may.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discurrent</ent>⟦br⟧
